Table 2. Total (nue,e-) and partial (nue,e- kn) cross sections and average 
emitted-neutron numbers, alpha = 3.0
 
The neutrino-induced reaction cross sections are given in units of 10^-42 cm^2 
and have been folded with normalized Fermi-Dirac distributions that are defined 
by their temperature parameter T and degeneracy parameter alpha.

alpha: degeneracy parameter of the Fermi-Dirac distribution (= 3.0 in this Table)
T: temperature (in MeV) of the Fermi-Dirac distribution
N: neutron number of the target nucleus; N = 41-135
Z: charge or proton number of the target nucleus; Z = 21-82
62Sc: mass number and element symbol of the target nucleus
(nue,e- ): total (nue,e-) reaction cross section 
(nue,e- 0n), (nue,e- 1n), ..., (nue,e- 8n): partial cross sections for emitting 
                                            0,1,...,7, and >=8 neutrons, 
                                            respectively, in the reaction
<n>: average number of neutrons emitted in the reaction
